<section class="section" id="events" aria-labelledby="events-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div id="events-anchor" class="section-anchor"></div>
    <div class="section-eyebrow" aria-hidden="true">Events</div>
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 id="events-heading">Dates that matter</h2>
      <span class="section-note">Deadlines · meetings · filings</span>
    </div>
    <p class="section-sub">The dates that move slowly until they don't. A few of these are legally binding. Most residents have never heard of them.</p>

    <div class="events-list" role="list">

      <div class="event-row" role="listitem">
        <div class="event-date">
          <div class="event-month">Apr</div>
          <div class="event-day" style="color:var(--red)">24</div>
        </div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-title">ADA Title II compliance deadline — all local government websites</div>
          <div class="event-detail">WCAG 2.1 AA required for all public entity websites under 28 C.F.R. Part 35. HB21-1110 applies to PDF documents. Zero district sites confirmed compliant on document accessibility. <strong>16 days.</strong></div>
        </div>
        <span class="event-badge eb-critical">Critical · 16 days</span>
      </div>

      <div class="event-row" role="listitem">
        <div class="event-date">
          <div class="event-month">Jul</div>
          <div class="event-day" style="color:var(--amber)">31</div>
        </div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-title">Annual audit due to Colorado State Auditor — all metro districts</div>
          <div class="event-detail">C.R.S. §32-1-106 requires annual audits submitted to the State Auditor by July 31. Currently, 0 of 8 audited districts post these publicly. The State Auditor sees it. Residents don't.</div>
        </div>
        <span class="event-badge eb-warn">High · Q3</span>
      </div>

      <div class="event-row" role="listitem">
        <div class="event-date">
          <div class="event-month">May</div>
          <div class="event-day">6</div>
        </div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-title">El Paso County BOCC regular meeting</div>
          <div class="event-detail">BOCC meetings are the primary venue for metro district oversight action. Draft BOCC resolution requiring service plans and audit docs on all district websites — full template in the citizen toolkit.</div>
        </div>
        <span class="event-badge eb-info">Meeting</span>
      </div>

      <div class="event-row" role="listitem">
        <div class="event-date">
          <div class="event-month">May</div>
          <div class="event-day">20</div>
        </div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-title">CORA response window closes — pending requests</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Two outstanding CORA requests (military housing numbers, district governance records). Colorado law requires response within 3 business days with up to 7-day extension. Response window tracked in CORA tracker.</div>
        </div>
        <span class="event-badge eb-warn">CORA deadline</span>
      </div>

      <div class="event-row" role="listitem">
        <div class="event-date">
          <div class="event-month">Jan</div>
          <div class="event-day">31</div>
        </div>
        <div class="event-body">
          <div class="event-title">BOCC proposed mandate — tagged PDFs on all district sites</div>
          <div class="event-detail">Proposed: BOCC resolution requiring all publicly posted PDFs to be WCAG 1.3.1 tagged by January 31, 2027. Currently zero sites comply. One resolution, 284 districts. <em>Proposed — not yet filed.</em></div>
        </div>
        <span class="event-badge eb-info">Proposed '27</span>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

